  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Kitchen Designer",
  "description": "<h2>Senior Kitchen Designer – Roles & Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Design modular kitchens and related interior solutions based on client requirements, space planning, and budget.</p></li><li><p>Conduct client consultations to understand needs, preferences, and functional requirements.</p></li><li><p>Prepare detailed kitchen layouts, elevations, and technical drawings using <strong>AutoCAD</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Create 3D designs and presentations; <strong>experience with Winner Design Software is an added advantage</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Present designs confidently to clients and explain materials, finishes, accessories, and appliances.</p></li><li><p>Handle end-to-end <strong>sales process</strong>, including quotations, negotiations, order closure, and coordination with the sales team.</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate design documentation, BOQs, and pricing details.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with production, installation, and project teams to ensure smooth execution and timely delivery.</p></li><li><p>Ensure <strong>cleanliness, organization, and visual appeal of the showroom</strong> at all times.</p></li><li><p>Display and maintain kitchen samples, catalogs, and design displays in a presentable manner.</p></li><li><p>Keep up to date with latest kitchen design trends, materials, and technologies.</p></li><li><p>Ensure high levels of customer satisfaction and handle client queries or design revisions professionally.</p></li><li><p>Mentor junior designers and provide technical guidance when required.</p></li><li><p>Follow company standards, design guidelines, and sales procedures.</p></li></ul>",
